From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Date: Thu 15 Mar 2001 12:55:43
Source: National News [edited
<http://www.stuff.co.nz/inl/index/0,1008,701389a11,FF.html>

NZ closes borders to EU animal products
---------------------------------------
New Zealand quarantine officials have slapped a ban on all animal product
imports from the European Union as foot-and-mouth disease continues to
spread. However, the Agriculture Ministry stressed yesterday that the move
was temporary because of a possible trade backlash.
The ministry said it was coincidental. Ministry biosecurity spokesman Derek
Belton said the "temporary suspension" would be reassessed in 30 days.
[FMD could wipe out $10 billion of New Zealand's export earnings overnight
if it spread here. It has cost Britain tens of billions of pounds since it
was first spotted on 22 Feb 2001. The British tourist industry will lose up
to 2 billion euros (NZ$7.1 billion) alone during Easter.
Products covered by the ban included meat and dairy products, byproducts,
semen, embryos and live cloven-hoofed animals. Visitors from EU countries
would now receive the heightened attention given to passengers from other
countries where foot-and-mouth is active, he said.
